original: Kjellbo, Nils Alfred, direktör, Göteborg, f. 11/11/94 i Kumla av Erik K. o. Matliilda Lindblom. G. 20 m. Elsa Jonsson. Barn: Birgit f. 21, g. rn. assuranstj :man Sture Tingström, Gbg, Hans-Erik 27, ’Stud. — Stud:ex. i Västerås 13, Gbgs lTan’d:inst. 13-14, res:-offrex. 16. Res. t. Tyskl., Polen, Tjec-koslov. o. Ungern 34, Finl. o. Estl. 35, Engl. 38. Anst. v. Husqvarna Vapen-fabr. A-B 14, chef f. dess sv. försälj-niavd. 19-37, verkst. dir. v. Husqvarna Fabr rlager A-B i Gbg sed. 38. Brand-chef i Husqvarna 24-37. Medl. av Frimurarorden, Par Bricoile m. fl. Hobbv: sikytte. SvmifbGM, SvsibSM, FMM.
translated: Kjellbo, Nils Alfred, director, Gothenburg, b. 11/11/94 in Kumla to Erik K. and Matliilda Lindblom. M. since 1920 with Elsa Jonsson. Children: Birgit b. 1921, married to insurance agent Sture Tingström, Gothenburg; Hans-Erik b. 1927, studying. Graduated from Västerås in 1913, Gothenburg Naval Institute in 1913-1914, reserve officer training in 1916. Traveled to Germany, Poland, Czechoslovakia, and Hungary in 1934; Finland and Estonia in 1935; England in 1938. Employed by Husqvarna Vapenfabrik AB in 1914, head of Swedish sales department from 1919-1937, executive director of Husqvarna Fabrik Lager AB in Gothenburg since 1938. Fire chief in Husqvarna from 1924-1937. Member of Freemasonry, Par Bricoile, and others. Hobby: shooting. Has been awarded SvmifbGM, SvsibSM, FMM.
